{% extends "sitebase.njk" %}

{% block title %}Orbii Knowledge - A Knowledge Sharing Platform{% endblock %}

{% block site_content %}
  
  <!-- Marketing section to attract developers and contributors -->
  <h2>Orbii Knowledge - Version 1.0: Join the Contributor Community</h2>
  <p>
    Orbii Knowledge is a fully open-source platform, created by Pejman Gohari, with the valuable help of Armin Kiany, CEO of <a href="https://www.edclub.com">EdClub</a>. Available on <a href="https://github.com/pejmang/Orbii-blog">GitHub</a>, Orbii Knowledge focuses on sharing knowledge in a simple and effective way, through a minimalist interface. 
  </p>
  <p>
    This platform is in its initial version and still needs to evolve with new features. However, it already offers a solid foundation for publishing articles with a focus on simplicity, speed, and accessibility. Based on the 11ty (Eleventy) static site generator, Orbii Knowledge is easy to customize and use for any type of content.
  </p>
  <p>
    Whether you're a developer, content architect, or a knowledge-sharing enthusiast, join a dynamic community and contribute to improving Orbii Knowledge. We believe in collective power to evolve this platform into something greater.
  </p>
  <p>
    You will have the opportunity to bring your ideas, develop new features, and enhance the user experience. Joining Orbii Knowledge means being part of an open-source project accessible to all, where every contribution matters.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Why Contribute?</h2>
  <p>
    By contributing to Orbii Knowledge, you will have the opportunity to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Take part in the evolution of a platform used by an international community of content creators.</li>
    <li>Enhance existing features or propose new ones to meet the community's needs.</li>
    <li>Connect with developers and creators sharing the same goals.</li>
    <li>Work with modern technologies like 11ty, Node.js, and continuous integration tools.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Your contribution can make a real difference in the future of Orbii Knowledge and open new possibilities in the world of simple and accessible blogging.
  </p>
  
  <!-- Technical Section and Contribution Process -->
  <h2>How to Contribute to Orbii Knowledge?</h2>
  <p>
    Whether you want to contribute to the source code, design templates, or optimize performance, we need your skills. Here are the various ways you can participate:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Feature Development:</strong> Help us add new features or improve existing ones.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong> Contribute to making the platform even faster and more responsive by improving front-end or back-end performance.</li>
    <li><strong>Design and Customization:</strong> Create new templates or improve existing designs to enhance user experience.</li>
    <li><strong>Documentation Writing:</strong> Help write clear and comprehensive guides to make the platform easier to use for other users and contributors.</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>Contribution Process</h3>
  <p>
    Contributing to Orbii Knowledge is simple and accessible. Here's how you can get started:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Clone the Orbii Knowledge GitHub repository from <a href="https://github.com/pejmang/Orbii-blog">this link</a>.</li>
    <li>Create a new branch for your contribution to work safely.</li>
    <li>Make your changes and submit a pull request explaining the changes you've made.</li>
    <li>Your contribution will be reviewed by our team before being merged into the main project.</li>
  </ol>
  
  <p>
    We look forward to seeing what you will bring to Orbii Knowledge, and we thank you for your participation in this open-source project.
  </p>

  <h3>Join Us</h3>
  <p>
    If you have ideas, suggestions, or questions, feel free to contact us or open a ticket on our GitHub repository. Together, let's make Orbii Knowledge an even more powerful and accessible platform for everyone.
  </p>

